      <text>It seems the paths have changed a little in this area, some have been reclaimed by nature with persistent mini-ponds. I used to avoid it in fall-winter due to muddiness, but now it was even overflown in August 2024 when I ran by. Some other informal paths seem to have come into existence from people trying to push their way through on other sides. Would need a proper GPS survey (and decision whether it is a one summer flooding kind of thing or the new normal on that path), but I cannot do it due to not living in the area any more.</text>
      <html>&lt;p&gt;It seems the paths have changed a little in this area, some have been reclaimed by nature with persistent mini-ponds. I used to avoid it in fall-winter due to muddiness, but now it was even overflown in August 2024 when I ran by. Some other informal paths seem to have come into existence from people trying to push their way through on other sides. Would need a proper GPS survey (and decision whether it is a one summer flooding kind of thing or the new normal on that path), but I cannot do it due to not living in the area any more.&lt;/p&gt;</html>
